text: Richard Woking (fl. 1404–1426), of Guildford, Surrey, was an English politician. He was a Member (MP) of the Parliament of England for Guildford in 1420 and December 1421. He was Mayor of Guildford in 1417–18, 1422–23, and 1425–26.http://www.historyofparliamentonline.org/volume/1386-1421/member/woking- richard ==References== Category:14th-century births Category:15th-century deaths Category:Mayors of places in Surrey Category:14th-century English people Category:English MPs 1420 Category:People from Sussex Category:English MPs December 1421 Category:Members of Parliament for Guildford
